==English==
{{wikipediapar|Allahu Akbar}}
===Etymology===
From Arabic [[الله]] ([[Allah]]/[[God]]) and [[أكبر]] (’ákbar, [[greater]]/[[greatest]]), the [[elative]] ([[comparative]]/[[superlative]]) of [[كبير]] (kibí:r, [[big]]).

===Phrase===
'''Allahu akbar'''

#(''Islam'') the [[Muslim]] [[takbir]] ([[proclamation]]) "[[God]] is most [[great]]"

